snippet: State officials plan to cancel coverage for about 10,500 people participating in the state health insurance exchange because they could not prove that they were citizens or legal residents of the United States.
abstract: Covered California, state-run insurance exchange, says they plan to cancel coverage for about 10,500 people who did not provide proof of citizenship or legal residency necessary to be covered under the Affordable Care Act; follows similar actions in Florida and Texas.
lead_paragraph: State officials plan to cancel coverage for about 10,500 people participating in the state health insurance exchange because they could not prove that they were citizens or legal residents of the United States.
